Industries






The breadth of the industry experience of Bain Capital Private Equity's professionals and the extent of our resources allows the firm to make strategic investments across a wide range of industries. Over the course of our history Bain Capital Private Equity has developed specialized expertise in key industry groups that allows the firm to further build its transaction flow, increase the effectiveness of its due diligence, and bring more substantial benefits to its portfolio companies.
 








  
 consumer, retail & dining  

  
 financial & business services  

  
 healthcare  

  
 industrial & energy  

  
 technology, media & telecom  

 














































Regions | Bain Capital Private Equity














Skip to main content 




Bain Capital Private Equity









⋮

Private Equity
Credit
Ventures
Public Equity



 




 











Regions






Our global Private Equity team operates across 9 offices on three continents including Boston, New York, London, Munich, Hong Kong, Shanghai, Tokyo, Mumbai and Sydney. In each territory, Bain Capital Private Equity applies the same proven investment philosophy and approach applied to local dynamics that the firm has successfully deployed over the last 30 years.
 









  
  

North America 
 The North American Region, with offices in Boston and New York, started in 1984. 



  
  

EMEA 
 The EMEA Region, with offices in London and Munich, started in 2000. 



  
  

Asia Pacific 
 The Asia Pacific Region, with offices in Hong Kong, Mumbai, Shanghai and Tokyo, started in 2005. 


 


































Bain Capital Europe Fund III LP




















Bain Capital Europe Fund III LP
2.80K



John Cook
08/23/12 10:42AM

Filed to: Bain files

Bain files
Mitt Romney






These documents are part of a package on Mitt Romney's Bain holdings. For the full report, go here.The Bain Files: Inside Mitt Romney's Tax-Dodging Cayman SchemesMitt Romney's $250 million fortune is largely a black hole: Aside from the meager and vague…Bain Capital Europe Fund III LP is general partnership based in the Cayman Islands. As of 2009, it held $287 million in assets (denominated in Euros) and reported an $11 million decrease in capital for the year.In 2011, the Ann D. Romney Blind Trust held between $50,000 and $100,000 in the fund, and reported zero income from it. The 2010 return of the Ann Romney Trust reported income from the fund's general partner, Bain Capital Partners Europe III LP.If you have any thoughts on, or information about, these documents, please enter the discussion here.


















































